<sec id="sec_6.7.2" xmlns:as="http://niso-sts-authoring-solution/authoring-schema" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:tbx="urn:iso:std:iso:30042:ed-1"><label>6.7.2</label><title>Types of instructions</title><p>The following instructions shall be supplied with each rig:</p><list list-type="alpha-lower"><list-item><label>a)</label><p>operator's instructions, 6.5.4;</p></list-item><list-item><label>b)</label><p>transport instructions, 6.5.5;</p></list-item><list-item><label>c)</label><p>assembly instructions, where applicable, 6.5.6;</p></list-item><list-item><label>d)</label><p>maintenance instructions, 6.5.7;</p></list-item><list-item><label>e)</label><p>spare parts list, 6.5.8.</p></list-item></list><p>The operator's instructions shall be available in a dedicated place on the machine.</p><p>Each instruction handbook shall contain the web address to the manufacturer and other contact details.</p></sec>
